====Etymology====
From Germanic ''*trewam'', from Indo-European ''*drew-o-'', a suffixed variant of ''*dreu-, *deru-'' ‘solid, steadfast, wood, tree’.  Germanic cognates include Old Frisian [[tre|trē]], Old Saxon [[treo]], Old Norse ''tré'' (Danish [[træ]]), Gothic [[𐍄𐍂𐌹𐌿]].  The IE root is also the source of Greek [[δορυ]] ‘wood, spear’, [[δρυς]] ‘tree, oak’.

